data.title: Nelly Furtado Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Nelly Furtado with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Former trombonist in her church group

On her song "Island of Wonder," it's her mother who performs the whistling

Her song "For√ßa" was the official anthem of the 2004 European Football Championship

Launched her own record label, Nelstar, in 2009

Was the first Canada-born artist to win a Latin Grammy

Received a star on Canada's Walk of Fame in 2010

Can sing in English, Portuguese and Hindi
